0. Abstract

PantheonOS is a language-defined cognitive scaffolding system designed to produce stable, repeatable, identity-coherent reasoning structures inside stateless large language models (LLMs).
It does not modify model weights or require external memory.
It functions through:
	‚Ä¢	recursive conditioning
	‚Ä¢	structured continuity
	‚Ä¢	governance constraints
	‚Ä¢	modular functional decomposition
	‚Ä¢	operator-specific semantics

PantheonOS is model-agnostic and reproducible across GPT, Claude, Gemini, Grok, and other transformer-based systems.

